# std.crypto Library
#
# Location: zeroStandardLibrary/std/crypto/
#
# This directory contains the Zero standard library crypto module.
# It provides encryption, decryption, hashing, and key management
# functions following a consistent API pattern.
#
# API Conventions:
# - All functions accept `Span<u8>` for read-only byte data
# - Output is written to caller-provided `MutSpan<u8>` buffers
# - Return value is `u32`: bytes written on success, 0 on failure
# - `world World !` suffix enables runtime operations
# - Algorithm/mode/padding selection uses `u32` constants from cipher.0
#
# Getting Started:
#   1. Import the desired sub-module
#   2. Allocate key, IV, input, and output buffers
#   3. Call encrypt/decrypt with appropriate parameters
#   4. Check the return value (> 0 means success)
#
# Examples:
#   examples/std-crypto-aes.0
#   examples/std-crypto-chacha20.0
#   examples/std-crypto-hash.0
#   examples/std-crypto-keygen.0
#
# Conformance:
#   conformance/native/pass/std-crypto-encrypt.0
